            <div type="positioning">
               <p>
                  <geo>35°39'N 05°30'W</geo>
                  <country>Morocco</country>
               </p>
            </div>

            <div type="typology">
               <p rend="typology">West (Maghreb) › Morocco › Northern type</p>
               <p>Pre-Hilali sedentary dialect</p>
            </div>

            <div type="general">
               <p>Anjra is a small town near the city of Tétouan in the Jbala region. The dialect of Anjra presents features that are unique or at least rarely found in other North African Arabic dialects.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p>All available studies on the dialect of Anjra have been made by the Spanish dialectologist Ángeles Vicente. Vicente 1996 presents six texts in the dialect of Anjra, with Spanish translation. Vicente 1998 is a short grammatical sketch of the dialect. The most comprehensive study on Anjra’s dialect is <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:IINYFKZM">Vicente (2000)</rs>, which includes chapters on phonology as well as verbal and nominal morphology: it also has 110 texts with Spanish translation. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:KMS4RHAT">Vicente (2002)</rs> is a brief article on gender-specific speech in the dialect of Anjra.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="dictionaries">
               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:IINYFKZM">Vicente (2000)</rs> includes a 43-page glossary.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="bibliography">               
                    <p xml:space="preserve">To view publications on this variety click <rs type="bibl" ref="bibl:geo:Anjra">here</rs>.</p>
